2024/12/16 13:39:11 Commit: {"did":"did:plc:43ku4dc2gtcryj3hdf465ang","time_us":1734356351904466,"kind":"commit","commit":{"rev":"3ldghb63xyw2g","operation":"create","collection":"app.bsky.feed.post","rkey":"3ldghb5quuk24","record":{"$type":"app.bsky.feed.post","createdAt":"2024-12-16T13:39:11.282Z","langs":["en"],"reply":{"parent":{"cid":"bafyreifvn3wouyi46vpmrarkv2vzngalvxqtglb6itzo6fbg7akuefdqhe","uri":"at://did:plc:wxe224kl2yklhrpj2friwiue/app.bsky.feed.post/3ldgerwjug22t"},"root":{"cid":"bafyreia7n7agsqyiqywhal5iqo76hycxgch35k6flgv4rkaxfadh2lzfue","uri":"at://did:plc:wxe224kl2yklhrpj2friwiue/app.bsky.feed.post/3ldge34nbbs2b"}},"text":"Overall this strikes me as good work—they've cut out young stars by noting that stars with unknown rotation periods are typically slow rotators, and so what's left should be mostly older stars like the Sun.\n\nBut I agree that these superflares might nonetheless be nonrepresentative."},"cid":"bafyreidxnaonlmssf5fi7l32kql5rbr4lefujjxvm7ca5cvhm6zb53ithi"}}
2024/12/16 13:39:11 Post: {"PostID":"3ldghb5quuk24","CreatorDid":"did:plc:43ku4dc2gtcryj3hdf465ang","CreatedAt":"2024-12-16T13:39:11.282Z","Text":"Overall this strikes me as good work—they've cut out young stars by noting that stars with unknown rotation periods are typically slow rotators, and so what's left should be mostly older stars like the Sun.\n\nBut I agree that these superflares might nonetheless be nonrepresentative.","Tags":[]}
2024/12/16 13:39:11 Commit: {"did":"did:plc:43ku4dc2gtcryj3hdf465ang","time_us":1734356351904990,"kind":"commit","commit":{"rev":"3ldghb63xyw2g","operation":"create","collection":"app.bsky.feed.post","rkey":"3ldghb5tul224","record":{"$type":"app.bsky.feed.post","createdAt":"2024-12-16T13:39:11.283Z","langs":["en"],"reply":{"parent":{"cid":"bafyreidxnaonlmssf5fi7l32kql5rbr4lefujjxvm7ca5cvhm6zb53ithi","uri":"at://did:plc:43ku4dc2gtcryj3hdf465ang/app.bsky.feed.post/3ldghb5quuk24"},"root":{"cid":"bafyreia7n7agsqyiqywhal5iqo76hycxgch35k6flgv4rkaxfadh2lzfue","uri":"at://did:plc:wxe224kl2yklhrpj2friwiue/app.bsky.feed.post/3ldge34nbbs2b"}},"text":"One concern I have is that some of their stars might be too faint for good rotation period measurements, even though they are fast rotators. It's unclear to me if they would detect superflares around stars this faint—if they would all the superflares could come from young stars or tight binaries."},"cid":"bafyreigfwtyzgbdzzop6qvburu23xxl4yawkmr7s4rz6t5mnjc5qlcsz6m"}}
2024/12/16 13:39:11 Post: {"PostID":"3ldghb5tul224","CreatorDid":"did:plc:43ku4dc2gtcryj3hdf465ang","CreatedAt":"2024-12-16T13:39:11.283Z","Text":"One concern I have is that some of their stars might be too faint for good rotation period measurements, even though they are fast rotators. It's unclear to me if they would detect superflares around stars this faint—if they would all the superflares could come from young stars or tight binaries.","Tags":[]}
2024/12/16 13:39:11 Commit: {"did":"did:plc:43ku4dc2gtcryj3hdf465ang","time_us":1734356351905724,"kind":"commit","commit":{"rev":"3ldghb63xyw2g","operation":"create","collection":"app.bsky.feed.post","rkey":"3ldghb5tvkc24","record":{"$type":"app.bsky.feed.post","createdAt":"2024-12-16T13:39:11.284Z","langs":["en"],"reply":{"parent":{"cid":"bafyreigfwtyzgbdzzop6qvburu23xxl4yawkmr7s4rz6t5mnjc5qlcsz6m","uri":"at://did:plc:43ku4dc2gtcryj3hdf465ang/app.bsky.feed.post/3ldghb5tul224"},"root":{"cid":"bafyreia7n7agsqyiqywhal5iqo76hycxgch35k6flgv4rkaxfadh2lzfue","uri":"at://did:plc:wxe224kl2yklhrpj2friwiue/app.bsky.feed.post/3ldge34nbbs2b"}},"text":"A bigger concern is that despite their cuts they still ended up with some fast rotators that flared many times. They removed these from the sample, but their presence suggests a hidden population of fast rotators, some of which might have flared only once, but nonetheless dominate their numbers."},"cid":"bafyreih5uencuik7zgmy4lht5gbbk4wnlqeddxekde2pxtbhkrgl6xvi6m"}}
2024/12/16 13:39:11 Post: {"PostID":"3ldghb5tvkc24","CreatorDid":"did:plc:43ku4dc2gtcryj3hdf465ang","CreatedAt":"2024-12-16T13:39:11.284Z","Text":"A bigger concern is that despite their cuts they still ended up with some fast rotators that flared many times. They removed these from the sample, but their presence suggests a hidden population of fast rotators, some of which might have flared only once, but nonetheless dominate their numbers.","Tags":[]}
