2024/12/16 13:39:54 Commit: {"did":"did:plc:bskjza4dbcc552d5p2skszpt","time_us":1734356394116412,"kind":"commit","commit":{"rev":"3ldghcgg5yf23","operation":"create","collection":"app.bsky.feed.post","rkey":"3ldghcg5qws27","record":{"$type":"app.bsky.feed.post","createdAt":"2024-12-16T13:39:53.648Z","langs":["en"],"reply":{"parent":{"cid":"bafyreig5oxmuf2oinqcjyej7sy4wu6nottbwdbbik35j5ulf52foss3y7y","uri":"at://did:plc:hewxr27p6lkudlzb3p4gkie3/app.bsky.feed.post/3ldgglnf4722p"},"root":{"cid":"bafyreig5oxmuf2oinqcjyej7sy4wu6nottbwdbbik35j5ulf52foss3y7y","uri":"at://did:plc:hewxr27p6lkudlzb3p4gkie3/app.bsky.feed.post/3ldgglnf4722p"}},"text":"If you ever windsurfed, you would know how pounding “chop” is, and how relatively smooth “waves” are. The damage comes from consistent slamming, not big waves breaking.\n\n“Chop” is resonant frequency is physics terms. My guess is the answer lies in researching “chop”, if you want greater detail."},"cid":"bafyreidchzpfm5iqairmv2tyooerl3zufg57bysg6zl6t2saqv5fpomr6u"}}
2024/12/16 13:39:54 Post: {"PostID":"3ldghcg5qws27","CreatorDid":"did:plc:bskjza4dbcc552d5p2skszpt","CreatedAt":"2024-12-16T13:39:53.648Z","Text":"If you ever windsurfed, you would know how pounding “chop” is, and how relatively smooth “waves” are. The damage comes from consistent slamming, not big waves breaking.\n\n“Chop” is resonant frequency is physics terms. My guess is the answer lies in researching “chop”, if you want greater detail.","Tags":[]}
